===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|日|辰|c1=s|c2=p|t1=sun|t2=time|ls=psc|ls2=ic}}. Originally written as {{zh-l|*辰}} alone; {{lang|zh|辰}} now refers primarily to one of the [[十二支|twelve earthly branches]].

===Etymology===
[[endopassive|Endopassive]] of {{och-l|震|to shake}} and {{och-l|振|to excite}}, from {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*dar ~ d(u/i)r||to tremble; to shiver}}, literally "to stir oneself" > "when life begins to stir" > "early morning" ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}). {{zh-ref|Smith (2011)}} relates {{zh-l|晨|early morning}} to {{zh-l|辰}} < *''dən'', the original form of {{zh-l|蜃|mollusc, clam}} < *''dəns'', as the rising sun looks ovoid due to atmospheric refraction.

